body_md:
This policy sets out how {{firm.name}} prevents bribery and corruption in line with the UK Bribery Act 2010, FCA expectations, and Ministry of Justice guidance.

Objectives:
- prohibit bribery, facilitation payments, and improper advantages.
- apply proportionate prevention controls and due diligence.
- manage gifts, hospitality, donations, and political activity.
- ensure escalation, investigation, and record keeping.

{% if abcRiskAreasList %}
Risk exposure in scope:
{{ abcRiskAreasList }}
{% endif %}

Gifts, hospitality, charitable donations, and political activity must never be used to secure improper advantage.

Controls include thresholds, pre-approvals, and mandatory recording in registers.

{% if abcGiftsRegister %}
A gifts and hospitality register is maintained and reviewed by Compliance.
{% endif %}
{% unless abcGiftsRegister %}
Gifts and hospitality approvals are logged by Compliance where a formal register is not maintained.
{% endunless %}

{% if abcPublicOfficials %}
Extra caution is required around public officials and live tenders, including pre-approval and enhanced due diligence.
{% endif %}

Associated persons such as agents and introducers create heightened risk. Red flags include success-only fees, opaque ownership, cash requests, or links to public officials.

Risk-tiered due diligence and contract controls are required before engagement.

{% if abcThirdParties %}
Third-party due diligence is completed before onboarding and refreshed at least annually.
{% endif %}
{% unless abcThirdParties %}
The firm does not use third-party introducers; any future use requires Compliance approval and due diligence.
{% endunless %}
